<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1421,762,787]" box="[151,1421,762,787]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[274,380,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Callicera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,380,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">Callicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from all other hover fly genera by the following combination of characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1118,834,1039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">• Antennae long; at least as long as the head, normally longer • Antennae with terminal style</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1118,834,1039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">• Entire body dark and without any yellow markings, in most cases metallic shining • Eyes haired</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1118,834,1039]" box="[151,578,978,1003]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">• Scutellum with ventral hair fringe</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1118,834,1039]" box="[151,632,1014,1039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">• Cross-vein r-m in basal half of cell dm</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
